1
00:00:07,916 --> 00:00:10,041
♪

2
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:13,666
[DERRIDA] The war’s become
even more devastating.

3
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,041
Everywhere you look,

4
00:00:16,125 --> 00:00:18,916
we’re on a path to destruction.

5
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:22,041
Is this...

6
00:00:22,125 --> 00:00:24,875
a result of me
changing the past?

7
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:31,000
-[cameras flashing]
-What now?

8
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:32,583
[grunt]

9
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,625
What can I do?

10
00:00:35,708 --> 00:00:37,541
What should I do?

11
00:02:15,541 --> 00:02:17,541
[wind blowing]

12
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:23,625
[VIDAUX]
Where do you think this

13
00:02:23,708 --> 00:02:25,916
“quiet place” is that
Cassiel mentioned?

14
00:02:26,916 --> 00:02:29,958
[groaning]

15
00:02:30,958 --> 00:02:32,541
[DERRIDA]
I don’t know yet.

16
00:02:32,625 --> 00:02:35,458
But I do have a place in mind
that could be a possibility.

17
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:37,291
Huh? What’s that?

18
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:40,208
[DERRIDA]
Yetz Engineering College.

19
00:02:40,291 --> 00:02:41,916
It’s my alma mater.

20
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:45,666
(engine starts up)

21
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,250
(engine humming)

22
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:51,541
[DERRIDA]
Mage...

23
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:54,625
Why are you researching
the Trout Theory?

24
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:56,750
It’s flawed and dangerous.

25
00:02:56,833 --> 00:03:00,000
If I’d listened back then
instead of simply refusing you,

26
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:02,000
could we have avoided
this whole thing?

27
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:04,750
I swear...

28
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,625
I’ll find you soon.

29
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:10,708
♪ ♪

30
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,291
[engines humming]

31
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,750
[GRAHAM] Suspicious behavior
from vehicles behind us.

32
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:19,166
-Number?
-[GRAHAM] Four detected.

33
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:21,583
[YURI]
Mayuka, stay hidden.

34
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:24,708
-[gunfire]
-[DERRIDA, YURI scream]

35
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:26,333
[VIDAUX]
Mouth shut, remember?

36
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:28,416
[tires screeching]

37
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:34,000
[gasp, grunt]

38
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:35,000
[BOTH scream]

39
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,458
[engines roaring]

40
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:43,833
-[gunfire]
-[tires screech]

41
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:46,041
-Autopilot!
-[GRAHAM] Roger.

42
00:03:46,125 --> 00:03:47,208
[beep]

43
00:03:47,291 --> 00:03:48,833
[gunfire]

44
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:51,125
-Ahh!
-[gunfire]

45
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,833
[explosion]

46
00:03:53,916 --> 00:03:56,625
-[yelling]
-[gunfire]

47
00:03:56,708 --> 00:03:58,416
[whimpering]

48
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,583
[clicking, whirring]

49
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:03,500
[tires screeching]

50
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:04,583
Ah!

51
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:06,500
[explosion]

52
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:08,333
-[tires screech]
-[explosion]

53
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,333
[GRAHAM] The two vehicles
behind us are closing in.

54
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:12,875
Safe route determined.

55
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:15,750
Leave the highway,
enter the mountain roads,

56
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,041
and at the first curve,

57
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:19,000
drive off the edge
into the forest below.

58
00:04:19,083 --> 00:04:21,000
Hold on!
How’s that safe, exactly?

59
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:23,625
[YURI] You’re telling us
to drive off a cliff?

60
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,250
[GRAHAM] My reinforced
plating can endure it.

61
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:26,333
[grunt]

62
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:27,666
[tires screech]

63
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:29,500
[engine roars]

64
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:31,833
[engines roar]

65
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,666
Everyone, prepare for impact!

66
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:38,208
[smash]

67
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,291
[BOTH groan]

68
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:42,916
[grunting]

69
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:48,833
♪ ♪

70
00:05:02,666 --> 00:05:03,666
[DERRIDA]
No sign of pursuit.

71
00:05:06,375 --> 00:05:08,291
[sighing]

72
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,750
We’ll wait it out
here until morning.

73
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,250
[DERRIDA]
Yeah. Sounds good.

74
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:14,666
[GRAHAM]
After weighing all outcomes,

75
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:17,250
this was the most
optimal choice available.

76
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:19,708
Hey, you okay?

77
00:05:19,791 --> 00:05:21,375
Hmm! Yeah, I’m good!

78
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:23,208
-[VIDAUX panting]
-[BOTH gasp]

79
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:24,458
[grunt]

80
00:05:24,541 --> 00:05:26,625
[MAYUKA]
Papa, you’re bleeding!

81
00:05:26,708 --> 00:05:28,250
[DERRIDA]
We need to treat him, now.

82
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:30,625
No, it’s nothing. I’m fine.
Just stings a little.

83
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:33,166
[DERRIDA]
You’re definitely not fine!

84
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:35,416
[sigh]
Where’s the medical kit in here?

85
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,500
[YURI]
Move aside, let me handle it.

86
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:38,583
[water flowing]

87
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:40,666
[insects chirping]

88
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:44,458
[groaning, wincing]

89
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:46,375
I’ll work quickly.

90
00:05:46,458 --> 00:05:48,000
Yeah. Alright.

91
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,958
[VIDAUX sigh, wincing]

92
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:53,375
[groaning continues]

93
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:54,958
Papa...

94
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
[insects chirping]

95
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,666
Wonder if there’s any
fresh water nearby.

96
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,625
[MAYUKA]
Is Papa going to be alright?

97
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:08,208
Mmm.

98
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:11,333
We just have to wait for
the medicine to kick in.

99
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:13,708
He needs to lie still
for a while, that’s all.

100
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:14,583
[chuckle]

101
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:16,291
Okay!

102
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:18,166
That’s good, then!

103
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,125
[sigh]

104
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:21,750
Hey, what’s wrong?

105
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,541
Are you still worried?

106
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:26,666
I swear, it’ll be okay.

107
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:27,583
Mmm.

108
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:29,500
Mmm.

109
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:31,083
Huh?

110
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:35,500
[VIDAUX groans, sighs]

111
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,125
[gasp]

112
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:40,750
[DERRIDA]
So many scars.

113
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,083
If it weren’t for
the war, maybe...

114
00:06:44,166 --> 00:06:45,708
♪

115
00:06:45,791 --> 00:06:47,083
[DERRIDA]
Vidaux.

116
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:48,291
Hmm?

117
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:52,041
Listen,

118
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:53,791
wouldn’t it be better to drop
off Mayuka somewhere safe?

119
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:55,583
[VIDAUX]
Hmm?

120
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,958
[DERRIDA] I know it’s
dangerous everywhere, but...

121
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:01,458
there must be someplace
better than with us.

122
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:04,083
Like back with that mechanic
friend of yours, Klaus.

123
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,416
[VIDAUX] And you really
think she’ll be safe there?

124
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,250
No, not totally. But still, I--

125
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,458
[VIDAUX] If you’re going to
lecture me, you can leave.

126
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:14,916
I’m sorry.

127
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:20,458
[rock bounces]

128
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:23,125
♪

129
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:25,833
[MAYUKA]
Papa never keeps himself safe.

130
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:27,500
[YURI] But if it weren’t
for him, the rest of us

131
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:29,416
wouldn’t have made it this far!

132
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,958
I’m grateful.

133
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:32,541
Yeah...

134
00:07:33,708 --> 00:07:35,250
[YURI]
Mayuka,

135
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:37,416
would you like it if you had
more time to play with him?

136
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:38,875
Huh?

137
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,125
Hmm...

138
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:42,791
Yeah! Why wouldn’t I?

139
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:44,666
Did you get to play
with your papa?

140
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:46,375
Mmm.

141
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:49,000
My dad’s actually the one who
taught me about photography.

142
00:07:49,083 --> 00:07:51,291
We’d go out
and take pictures together.

143
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:54,250
You’re so mature for your age.

144
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:55,750
Do you ever get lonely?

145
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,583
[MAYUKA]
Hmm...

146
00:07:57,666 --> 00:08:00,583
Sometimes, but at least
I have my books.

147
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:01,958
When Papa’s off doing stuff,

148
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:04,666
I always have stories
to keep me company.

149
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,708
♪

150
00:08:09,541 --> 00:08:10,916
Reading books,

151
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,166
I can imagine all
kinds of things.

152
00:08:14,166 --> 00:08:17,166
And when a page is missing,
I make up what happened!

153
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:23,833
Sometimes Papa doesn’t come
back for two or three days,

154
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:27,416
so I have lots of time to think
about the stories I’ve read.

155
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:34,958
When I grow up, I’ll put them
together and be a writer!

156
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:37,208
[laugh]
That’s great!

157
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:38,791
[MAYUKA]
I wanna be a good writer

158
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:40,541
and make lots of money for Papa.

159
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,625
I’m only here because of him,

160
00:08:42,708 --> 00:08:45,041
so I need to do what I can.

161
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:56,166
♪

162
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,916
Well, I’ll be your first fan!

163
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,375
-I promise.
-[MAYUKA giggles]

164
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:07,125
[MAYUKA]
Is that a firefly?

165
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,541
[YURI]
Huh? Oh, it is!

166
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,833
[gasp]

167
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:13,541
I’ve never seen
real ones before!

168
00:09:17,083 --> 00:09:18,750
[gasp]

169
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:19,958
[giggle]

170
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:22,041
[shutter snapping]

171
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:26,458
-[snap]
-[MAYUKA gasps]

172
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,333
-[snap]
-[MAYUKA giggles]

173
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:31,416
-[footsteps]
-[giggle]

174
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,500
You all done?

175
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:33,916
Huh?

176
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,833
Yeah.

177
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:37,833
[sigh]

178
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:40,083
-[DERRIDA] I made Vidaux upset.
-Huh?

179
00:09:40,166 --> 00:09:41,916
You couldn’t bandage
him up right?

180
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,416
It’s not that.
It’s about Mayuka.

181
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,333
-Huh?
-It’s not my place,

182
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:48,583
but I’m worried that
she isn’t safe with us.

183
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:49,833
You’ve got a point.

184
00:09:49,916 --> 00:09:51,875
I’m no dad,

185
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:54,291
but should you really take
your kid everywhere with you,

186
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,166
-even if it’s dangerous?
-Well, I mean...

187
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,416
It’s weird,

188
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,666
but I assumed
there was a reason.

189
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:02,375
Something that we just
don’t understand.

190
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:03,250
[MAYUKA humming]

191
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,666
[DERRIDA]
A reason...

192
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,625
[YURI] I don’t know
what it could be, though,

193
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:08,375
or if it’s any
of our business.

194
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,458
[groaning]

195
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:13,458
[MAN] Inspector Vidaux
has it under control.

196
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:15,208
He’s arrested the culprit!

197
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:18,083
You’re doing truly
incredible work out there.

198
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:19,791
It’s nice to know I have
a man in the field

199
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,625
I can always count on.

200
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:22,458
[thud]

201
00:10:22,541 --> 00:10:24,166
♪

202
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:26,458
All that guy cares about is
getting good press for himself.

203
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:27,750
What a freakin’ joke!

204
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,458
You’re telling me!
I can’t stand him.

205
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:31,250
Never responds to
our calls for backup,

206
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:33,125
but he’s always there to
take the credit, isn’t he?

207
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:35,708
Don’t be concerned
with that crap.

208
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:37,250
Our job is to catch bad guys,

209
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,916
and see that they’re punished.

210
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,250
That’s all that matters.

211
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:43,000
Yeah, I mean... I guess so, sir.

212
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,708
-[phone vibrates]
-Uh--

213
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:47,458
[sigh]
Hello?

214
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,000
[gasp]

215
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:52,541
[COP]
Inspector!

216
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:04,625
[OFFICIAL] Regulations forbid
you from working on a case

217
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:06,416
that involves your own family.

218
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,458
[heavy breathing]

219
00:11:08,541 --> 00:11:10,041
♪

220
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:15,208
[REPORTER] A week has passed
since the hit-and-run incident,

221
00:11:15,291 --> 00:11:16,833
but still no suspects
have been identified...

222
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:19,333
The law is bullshit.

223
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:21,833
And justice is bullshit, too.

224
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,833
[VIDAUX] And neither of
them could protect my wife.

225
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:47,125
An eye for an eye.

226
00:11:47,208 --> 00:11:49,208
A tooth for a tooth.

227
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:13,833
The fate of all
sinners is punishment.

228
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,125
♪

229
00:12:18,208 --> 00:12:19,666
[lock creaks]

230
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,750
[cocks gun]

231
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,333
Let me teach you
this world’s rules.

232
00:12:24,416 --> 00:12:26,916
An eye for an eye.

233
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,333
A tooth for a tooth.

234
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:30,666
And so it follows...

235
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,666
[gunshot]

236
00:12:35,291 --> 00:12:37,583
that for a death a death.

237
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:39,541
[baby crying]

238
00:12:39,625 --> 00:12:41,125
Huh?

239
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:44,791
[continues crying]

240
00:12:48,875 --> 00:12:50,375
[gasp]

241
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:55,208
[sigh]

242
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:56,541
[crying continues]

243
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:03,166
[sigh]
That bastard Derrida.

244
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:06,250
Making me relive
those awful memories.

245
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:07,958
-[beeping]
-What is it, Graham?

246
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:11,458
[GRAHAM] Several armed machines
are rapidly approaching.

247
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,000
[grunt]

248
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,333
[GRAHAM]
DZs.

249
00:13:14,416 --> 00:13:15,875
[sigh]

250
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:18,458
[WOMAN, overlapping]
Clockwise. Anti-clockwise.

251
00:13:22,708 --> 00:13:25,625
♪

252
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:26,708
[DERRIDA]
What’s wrong?

253
00:13:26,791 --> 00:13:28,625
[VIDAUX]
DZs, incoming.

254
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,000
[sigh]

255
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:31,750
We’ll head out
before they’re on us.

256
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:32,875
[DERRIDA]
Mm-hmm.

257
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:35,458
[engine humming]

258
00:13:46,166 --> 00:13:47,416
Hmm...

259
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:52,750
[buzzing]

260
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,583
[DERRIDA]
Maybe 20 of them?

261
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:58,541
No, it looks like
even more than that.

262
00:13:58,625 --> 00:14:01,125
[VIDAUX] What do you think?
Another DZ graveyard?

263
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:02,666
[air rushing]

264
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,500
[thud, crunch]

265
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:06,166
So, what’ll we do?

266
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,666
[VIDAUX growls]

267
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,500
What do you think?
We plow through!

268
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:10,500
Ah!

269
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,083
[engine roars]

270
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:14,750
[gunfire]

271
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,833
[tires screeching]

272
00:14:18,583 --> 00:14:20,083
[gunfire]

273
00:14:20,166 --> 00:14:21,500
[tires screech]

274
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:22,916
[engine roars]

275
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,708
[groan]

276
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:26,041
[grunt]

277
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:26,958
Whoa!

278
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:29,166
-[bang]
-[whine]

279
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:30,875
[gunfire]

280
00:14:32,666 --> 00:14:34,666
[buzzing, hissing]

281
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,000
♪

282
00:14:37,083 --> 00:14:38,125
Ahead of us, too?

283
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:39,208
[gasp]

284
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:41,125
Damn junk!

285
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,791
[gunfire]

286
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:45,208
Graham! Any other weapons?

287
00:14:45,291 --> 00:14:47,000
[beeping]

288
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:49,000
What the--?

289
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:50,750
[DERRIDA]
You take the front!

290
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:54,500
[gunfire]

291
00:15:00,208 --> 00:15:01,583
[explosion]

292
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:02,958
-[explosion]
-[smash]

293
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:04,208
Got it!

294
00:15:04,291 --> 00:15:06,875
Don’t celebrate!
There’s more coming!

295
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:07,958
[DERRIDA]
I gotcha!

296
00:15:08,041 --> 00:15:09,166
-[gun clicking]
-[gasp]

297
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:10,791
Derrida, take this!

298
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:12,291
Thanks. Watch Mayuka!

299
00:15:12,375 --> 00:15:15,708
Pretty cocky. Be careful!
You’ll get yourself hurt.

300
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:18,666
Don’t you worry about me,
I’m here to watch your back!

301
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:19,750
-[blast]
-[explosion]

302
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:21,083
[hissing]

303
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:22,916
[GRAHAM]
Now there are approximately 20.

304
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,625
-What? Still that many?
-[whining]

305
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:25,875
Damn it!

306
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,458
-[blasting]
-[gunfire]

307
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,166
-[hissing]
-[thud]

308
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,083
[gasp]

309
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:33,333
-[crunch]
-[grunt]

310
00:15:34,541 --> 00:15:36,125
[groaning]

311
00:15:36,208 --> 00:15:38,000
No, Vidaux!

312
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,291
-[smashing]
-[grunting]

313
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:41,208
Papa, no!

314
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:44,166
[MAYUKA]
Come back...

315
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:48,625
Come back, Papa!

316
00:15:48,708 --> 00:15:51,625
[buzzing, hissing]

317
00:15:54,625 --> 00:15:56,125
[groaning]

318
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,500
Damn. Not good.

319
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:00,541
[slice]

320
00:16:01,541 --> 00:16:04,291
Vidaux fell off!
We have to go back!

321
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,750
Hurry! Save Papa, please!

322
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,958
-Graham, do it!
-[GRAHAM] Do what?

323
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:13,666
Go back! Right now! Save Papa!

324
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:14,583
[GRAHAM]
Roger that!

325
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:15,708
[engine roar]

326
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:16,625
[tires screech]

327
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:20,625
[wind blowing]

328
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:21,791
[VIDAUX]
The truth is,

329
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:24,083
I could've let her
go at any time.

330
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:27,500
I told myself that
nowhere was safe enough.

331
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:32,375
But, the real reason is...

332
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,083
-[MAYUKA] Papa!
-Huh?

333
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,666
-Get out of the way!
-[gasp]

334
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,333
[engine roaring]

335
00:16:38,416 --> 00:16:40,125
[smash, thud]

336
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,458
Duck, Vidaux!

337
00:16:42,541 --> 00:16:43,458
[gunfire]

338
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:44,916
[explosions]

339
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,416
[whining]

340
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:49,333
♪

341
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:51,416
[screaming]

342
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:53,833
[explosions]

343
00:16:53,916 --> 00:16:55,916
[screaming]

344
00:16:58,375 --> 00:16:59,625
[smash]

345
00:17:01,166 --> 00:17:02,375
[thud]

346
00:17:02,458 --> 00:17:04,458
[heavy breathing]

347
00:17:07,291 --> 00:17:09,333
It’s over.

348
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,750
[wind blowing]

349
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:19,000
[grunting]

350
00:17:19,083 --> 00:17:21,916
You kids really don’t know
how to play gentle, do you?

351
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,083
If you’re going to lecture me,
then you can leave.

352
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:25,375
Hmm...

353
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:27,458
[chuckle]

354
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:30,166
[water running]

355
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:33,250
♪

356
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,083
-[splash]
-[gasp]

357
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:40,666
-[YURI] Here. Take it.
-Huh?

358
00:17:41,666 --> 00:17:43,333
-Thank you.
-[giggle]

359
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,791
[footsteps]

360
00:17:48,041 --> 00:17:49,208
[MAYUKA]
Papa!

361
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,833
You okay, sweetheart?

362
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:53,250
[MAYUKA]
Yep. Thanks to you!

363
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,500
How about you though?

364
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:56,958
Oh, I’m fine.
Couldn’t be better.

365
00:17:57,041 --> 00:17:58,833
But it’s thanks to you,
this time.

366
00:17:58,916 --> 00:18:00,083
[giggle]

367
00:18:00,166 --> 00:18:01,625
Mayuka,

368
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:04,333
don’t you ever do anything
like that again, alright?

369
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,500
Aww!

370
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,583
Oh, I forgot!
I found something earlier

371
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:11,458
that I wanted to show you!

372
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:17,708
[giggle]

373
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:22,166
Aren’t they pretty?

374
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:24,458
They are. That’s for sure.

375
00:18:25,583 --> 00:18:27,791
But, Mayuka,
you should let them go.

376
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:29,000
Hmm?

377
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:32,208
Well, they can’t stay
in your hands forever,

378
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:33,291
now can they?

379
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:34,833
Huh?

380
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:37,250
♪

381
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,125
No, I guess not.

382
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:41,958
Bye-bye!

383
00:18:49,291 --> 00:18:50,416
Hmm?

384
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,833
[BOTH laugh]

385
00:18:53,916 --> 00:18:55,458
[VIDAUX]
Okay. Let’s take a short break,

386
00:18:55,541 --> 00:18:57,416
then head out again.

387
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,666
-[VIDAUX strains]
-[MAYUKA yelps]

388
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,916
-Papa, are you okay?
-[chuckle]

389
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,000
I can handle you easily, kid.

390
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:05,208
Huh?

391
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:07,083
I’ll be heavier
next year, though.

392
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:10,083
And I’ll be even bigger and
taller the next one after that!

393
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:13,291
But Papa can carry me.

394
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:15,083
Papa is strong.

395
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:16,416
[chuckle]

396
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:20,500
-[VIDAUX grunts]
-[MAYUKA yelps]

397
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:22,250
[BOTH laughing]

398
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:25,041
Yuri, what we were
talking about earlier...

399
00:19:25,125 --> 00:19:27,333
Uh-huh. I get you.

400
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,750
They’re a good family,
aren’t they?

401
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:30,958
[shutter snaps]

402
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:35,708
[DERRIDA]
Yeah.

403
00:19:39,958 --> 00:19:41,833
-[high-pitched whine]
-Huh?

404
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,916
[jet engines roar]

405
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,916
[DERRIDA]
Are those...

406
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:52,875
No, can it be?

407
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:59,166
[air raid siren]

408
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:01,291
[explosions]

409
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:06,625
[MAN]
It has begun.

410
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:09,708
♪

411
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,583
There’s no way.

412
00:20:14,666 --> 00:20:17,333
I can’t allow this!

413
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:18,916
I need to time ride again!

414
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,541
-I need to change the pa--
-[gasp]

415
00:20:20,625 --> 00:20:23,625
[ANGE] The time ride
is not all-powerful.

416
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:27,375
Changes to any given past
event can only be made once.

417
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,833
[DERRIDA]
Every time I go back,

418
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:34,375
I further limit my chances of
actually changing anything.

419
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:37,791
Wait a minute.

420
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:39,083
My memories...

421
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:41,416
Is this memory even reliable?

422
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:45,250
If I’m losing memories
because of the time rides,

423
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,250
then wouldn’t that mean...?

424
00:20:49,791 --> 00:20:51,583
[heavy breathing]

425
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:54,166
I don’t feel like
I’m missing anything.

426
00:20:56,375 --> 00:20:59,833
But, if I had lost my memories,

427
00:20:59,916 --> 00:21:01,916
would I even realize it?

428
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:07,041
♪

429
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:09,125
[WOMAN]
Sorry for the wait.

430
00:21:09,208 --> 00:21:11,833
Are you the one who
wanted to speak with me?

431
00:21:11,916 --> 00:21:14,416
[MAGE] It’s been quite a while,
Professor Marlene.

432
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,541
Uh?

433
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:18,041
We two met at my
father’s funeral,

434
00:21:18,125 --> 00:21:20,000
or don’t you remember?

435
00:21:20,083 --> 00:21:22,333
I’m Mage Bilstein.

436
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:25,875
[PROFESSOR]
Ah. Nathan’s girl.

437
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,250
[MAGE]
Please, Professor.

438
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:30,291
Teach me about
the Trout Theory.

439
00:21:31,291 --> 00:21:33,125
I need to understand it.

440
00:21:34,166 --> 00:21:35,625
I’m sorry, Mage.

441
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,875
But that is still
an unproven theory, you know.

442
00:21:38,958 --> 00:21:42,250
Accompanied by many unresolved
and dangerous issues.

443
00:21:44,875 --> 00:21:47,375
And even if it could
be utilized as intended,

444
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:50,208
it consumes incredible
amounts of fuel.

445
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:54,875
Are you certain you want to jump
back, knowing all of that?

446
00:21:54,958 --> 00:21:56,500
I do,

447
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:58,583
because I need to.

448
00:21:58,666 --> 00:22:00,583
There’s no other way.

